  "notes": "After six days (Luke: about eight) Jesus takes Peter, James, and John up a high mountain, is transfigured before them, and is joined by Moses and Elias; Peter offers three tabernacles, a cloud overshadows them, and a voice names the beloved Son and bids them hear him. As they come down he charges them to tell no man until the resurrection. Luke alone records the talk of his decease (9:31) and the disciples' sleep (9:32); Mark alone closes with their questioning what the rising meant (9:10); these are left unlinked.",
